VSangeetha Ksheerasagara celebrated late Uppalapati Ankayya&#8217;s birth anniversary  recently in Thyagaraya Gaana Sabha by featuring two classical music concerts by P.V. Subba Rao and Duddu Radhika.P.V. Subba Rao is the disciple of Dr. Pasupathi and Late N.S. Srinivasan.  He began his concert with Bhairaviata tala varnam,Viribhonisree Mahaganapathiin Naata, which was neatly sung with littleswaramin it.Enta Nerchina Saphalamoin Saveri withswaramwas effective. Thyagaraja&#8217;sKsheera Sagarain Devagandhari was not up to the mark. Dharmavathi was elaborated for a decentragamand Subba Rao tookParandhamavathiof Deekshitar inRupakamwith competitiveneravalin it. Shankarabharanam was elaborated in detail . Uma Shanker on the violin and kappa Srinivas on mridangam lent good support and maintained the spirit of the concert.Duddu Radhika paid rich tributes to the legendary musician late Uppalapati Ankayya. She began withSahana Varnamin Adi which set the tempo of the concert.Sarasiruhasnapriyein Natai was the next. Reetigowla was apt choice andChera ravaemiraof Thyagaraja was thekrithi.Sripathein Nageswaaravali was the fast number to come next. The main attraction of the day Madyamavathi. Theragamexpansion maintained theragabhavamand Radhika showed her improvement in her performances. Thygaraja&#8217;sRamakatha Sudhawas the krithi with interestingswaram. N.C. Anatha Krishna did very well with his violin accompaniment and Burra Sreeram on mridangam lent good support.
